    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nA paired extmark is not adjusted correctly when deleting the end of the mark.\r\n(There is no visual problem, just reporting this because it results in ~~un~~expected behavior in #25767 @bfredl)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" test.vim\r\nlet ns = nvim_create_namespace('')\r\ncall setline(1, repeat(['aaa bbb ccc'], 5))\r\ncall nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 2, 4, { 'id':1, 'hl_group' : 'Error', 'end_col':7, 'end_row':3 })\r\nnorm 4Gdd\r\nlet a = nvim_buf_get_extmark_by_id(0, ns, 1, {'details':1})[2]['end_row']\r\ncall setline(1, repeat(['aaa bbb ccc'], 5))\r\ncall nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 2, 4, { 'id':1, 'hl_group' : 'Error', 'end_col':7, 'end_row':3 })\r\nnorm 3Gdd\r\nlet b = nvim_buf_get_extmark_by_id(0, ns, 1, {'details':1})[2]['end_row']\r\necho a . ', ' . b\r\n```\r\n1. Run `nvim --clean -S test.vim`\r\n2. Observe that when line 4 (row 3), the end of the range, is deleted with <kbd>dd</kbd>, the end of the mark is not adjusted to row 2.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe extmark end row is adjusted correctly.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1482+g161e40848\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nst\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nst-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
